Project: Investigate a Dataset - [No-show appointments in Brazil]¶

Table of Contents¶

  • Introduction
  • Data Wrangling
  • Exploratory Data Analysis
  • Conclusions

Introduction¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row.

● ‘ScheduledDay’ tells us on what day the patient set up their appointment.

● ‘Neighborhood’ indicates the location of the hospital.

● ‘Scholarship’ indicateswhether or not the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program Bolsa Família.

● Be careful about the encoding of the last column: it says ‘No’ if the patient showed up to their appointment, and ‘Yes’ if they did not show up.

Dataset Description¶

noshowappointments-kagglev2-may-2016.csv

Question(s) for Analysis¶

What factors are important for us to know in order to predict if a patient will show up for their scheduled

appointment?¶

Research Question 2 : how the age could affect the attendance rate of patients?¶

In [115]:
#using matplotlip for visulization defenation of attendance rate.
# using the visualization plot for studing the affect of Age on the attendance rate and probability of attending.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


def attendance_rate(df,col_name,Attended,Not_attended):
    plt.figure(figsize=[11,5])
    df[col_name][Attended].hist(alpha=.7,bins=12,color="green",label="Attended patients")
    df[col_name][Not_attended].hist(alpha=.7,bins=12,color="orange",label="Not_attended patients")
    plt.legend();
    plt.title("Relationship between age and attendance rate of patients")
    plt.ylabel("Count of patients")
    plt.xlabel("Age of patients")
attendance_rate(df,"Age",Attended,Not_attended)

1-The histgraph show that the highest range of attended patients recorded for the childerens below 9 years,which reflect the care of babies by their families.

2-the second peak for the highest attendance were at age range from 47 to 57 years old.

#using the visualization plot bar graph for studing the affect of Gender on the attendance rate and probability of attending.

def attendance_rate(df,col_name,Attended,Not_attended):
    plt.figure(figsize=[12,7])
    df[col_name][Attended].value_counts().plot(kind='bar',alpha=.6,color="green",label="Attended patients")
    df[col_name][Not_attended].value_counts().plot(kind='bar',alpha=.6,color="red",label="Not_attended patients")
    plt.legend();
    plt.title("Relationship between Gender and attendance rate of patients")
    plt.ylabel("Count of patients")
    plt.xlabel("Gender of patients")
attendance_rate(df,"Gender",Attended,Not_attended)

1-The bar chart show that the patients count of Females are generaly higher than the males.

2- almost the forth of males and females did not attend in thier appointments.

3- no clear relationship between the type of gender of patient and the attendance rate.

Conclusions¶

Findings of project:¶

1-Age ranges could strongly affect the attendance rate of paitents, particularly two age ranges (0-9 years) &(47-57 years) whom acheaved the highest attendance rate.

2- the Neighbourhoods signifcantly affect the attendance rate.

3- SMS content and program is differ between the Neighbourhoods so the effect are significantly different which is very strong in some Neighbourhoods.

4- the percent of patients whom attend without SMS reciving higher than whom attend after reciving SMS, which indicate that the SMS program sholud be revised.

5- there is a weak effect of the Diabetes on the attendance rate.

Limitations during the project:¶

The effect of Many paramaters were studdied in this project but no clear relationship was observed between the attendance rate of patients and Gender, diabites, hypertension, alcoholism, or scholarship.
